    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="284"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.51/3837</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-01">February 1,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The German Ambassador came in and reported generally, but not in detail, the fact
                    that a settlement of the claims of American creditors of Germany had been
                    effected by agreement between both creditors and debtor. Mr. Phillips, who had
                    been handling the matter, was also present and we both expressed our special
                    satisfaction and gratification at this action.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador represented in this connection that the American Ambassador at
                    Berlin had by letter on January 25th stated to the German Government that the
                    American bondholders’ committee had <pb facs="0447" n="347" xml:id="pg_347"/>
                    been authorized to deal with the entire matter and was functioning
                    satisfactorily to the United States Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
